Providers can further improve this process and decrease the need to obtain PA.
Prescribers can:
• timely submit medical claims to Medicaid FFS and MMC Plans;
• ensure the accuracy of the claim information being transmitted;
• ensure code claims with all appropriate diagnosis, per the International Classification of Diseases
(ICD), and procedure codes that are most closely associated with the services provided:
up to 12 codes on professional claims;
up to 25 codes on institutional claims; and
up to five codes on prescriptions claims.

Pharmacies can:
• submit ICD codes to NYRx, if present on a prescription:
up to five codes can be submitted per the pharmacy transaction;
claims should be formatted without the decimal included;
ICD codes will be collected via the transaction and used for future claim approvals (the ICD
codes cannot be leveraged on the same day of service).
